dataIdInfo.idPurp: Polygon Feature Class contains 6f boundary information both federal grants that follow LWCF rules. LWCF requires parks funded by LWCF to be held in recreational use in purpetuity and 6f(3) maps determine the area that is included in this purpetuity requirement.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
projectNum - The project number that the polygon is associated with.

landContro - The type of land control that the sponsor has on the property, own, lease, special user permit or a combination.

type - The type of 6f boundary it is.

  • Past - Previous version of the boundary that was overridden by a contract amendment

  • Current - Current version of the boundary that has the LWCF requirements for recreational perpetuity

replacemen - indicates if the polygon represents a replacement property that was used to replace land that was converted out of the recreational purpetuity requirement.

year - The year that the boundary was created.

parkNum - The unique park number of the park that the boundary is associated with

coverage - Tells if the boundary included the entire park when the grant was given or if it only included a subset of the park when the grant was given.

amend - Tells if the boundary is associated with a conversion project amendment.

stamp - Tells if the boundary map for this park and project has a 6f offical stamp on it.

source - The source of information that was used to generate the boundary.

note1 - General notes about the boundary.

note2 - Continued general notes about the boundary.

acresGIS - The area of the polygon in acres according to the GIS geometry

acresAcc - The acres of the polygon in acres according to deeds, project papers, sponsor contact and other information.

Maintenance instructions

As each grant, cycle passes the project boundaries change when projects close. Please replace the shape from the project boundary feature with the shape from the sec6f3Draft feature class. Then delete the draft feature because the draft is no longer a draft.

Coordinate system is NAD_1983_UTM_Zone_15N
